at|^b@2djneill: The topic of today's lesson is handling intererence over our 1@c opening.

That is when the opponents overcall our 1@c, or double it, or even overcall over a 1@c - 1@d response

Just to review, 1@c-1@d  is 0-7 HCP

Now, it's not too hard to handle when we have made a positive response
e.g. 1@c - 1@h   (8-11) - and now they bid 2@c

It's still the same idea, we bid our PRIMARY SUITS first, and get to the right game
But we have the extra juicy chance of penalizing the opponents

Whenever we make a POSITIVE response, GAME GOING, doubles are penalty.

So today I'm going to talk about the difficult situation where we don't know if we have game or not.


Let's start with 1@c - (Pass) - 1@d|


